                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/567: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-06T09:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1921—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. A revolution through the Army began at midnight ending five this morning
                    overthrowing Herrera government. Generals Orellana, Lima, and Larrave head a
                    provisional government. President Herrera prisoner in his home. All his Cabinet
                    in military prison. About a dozen killed by police resistance. Many natives
                    arrested. City quiet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
